284
00:12:42,109 --> 00:12:45,806
Steal.

285
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,352
Good job, Assistant.

286
00:12:51,353 --> 00:12:52,801
We're going to jump down from here.

287
00:12:53,495 --> 00:12:54,789
My necklace!

288
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:57,108
Even though I do not know what it is,

289
00:12:57,109 --> 00:13:00,097
I can't let you take it away.

290
00:13:00,098 --> 00:13:02,805
Up until the very end, that guy…

291
00:13:02,806 --> 00:13:04,300
Seal.

292
00:13:04,301 --> 00:13:09,009
All jerks!

293
00:13:13,504 --> 00:13:15,294
S-So cool.

294
00:13:21,901 --> 00:13:25,509
Calm down, calm down.

295
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:27,373
It's splitting, it's splitting!

296
00:13:27,374 --> 00:13:28,591
My head is splitting!

297
00:13:28,592 --> 00:13:31,409
I'm just being instigated.

298
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:33,196
The mastermind is Chris!

299
00:13:33,706 --> 00:13:35,201
You! Damn you!

300
00:13:35,202 --> 00:13:36,689
That hurts.

301
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:38,310
You said the reason for making a fuss

302
00:13:38,311 --> 00:13:40,603
is to get back
a dangerous sacred treasure?

303
00:13:41,199 --> 00:13:43,510
Why did not you tell me from the start?

304
00:13:43,992 --> 00:13:47,409
It must have been very hard for you

305
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,800
if you found out that
he and I were working together.

306
00:13:49,801 --> 00:13:51,495
That hurts!

307
00:13:51,496 --> 00:13:54,405
Hey, you are not supposed to talk, okay?

308
00:13:56,209 --> 00:13:57,585
Geez.

309
00:13:58,201 --> 00:14:00,297
Is there anything else you're hiding?

310
00:14:02,705 --> 00:14:04,504
It seems there is.

311
00:14:07,399 --> 00:14:08,894
What's this?

312
00:14:09,702 --> 00:14:12,809
Because working together
increases the chances of success.

313
00:14:13,393 --> 00:14:14,456
Why do your Steal

314
00:14:14,457 --> 00:14:16,409
keep stealing things that you shouldn't?

315
00:14:16,410 --> 00:14:18,397
It's not underwear this time.

316
00:14:18,398 --> 00:14:20,306
That's not the issue here.

317
00:14:23,707 --> 00:14:24,905
Listen carefully, Kazuma.

318
00:14:25,509 --> 00:14:28,201
You must never lose this ring.

319
00:14:28,202 --> 00:14:31,098
And don't let anyone find out about it.

320
00:14:31,099 --> 00:14:32,493
Take it with you to the grave.

321
00:14:32,494 --> 00:14:34,003
Hey, don't be like that.

322
00:14:34,004 --> 00:14:35,206
As this is a very important item,

323
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:36,197
I will simply say that I found it nearby

324
00:14:36,198 --> 00:14:37,832
and am now going to return it.

325
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:38,383
Idiot!

326
00:14:38,384 --> 00:14:39,103
That hurts!

327
00:14:39,410 --> 00:14:42,805
It is something that should be
given to a future spouse

328
00:14:42,806 --> 00:14:44,785
and can only be taken off
when an engagement is confirmed.

329
00:14:46,398 --> 00:14:48,300
But to think that it was stolen by thieves

330
00:14:48,301 --> 00:14:50,806
and found by adventurers nearby?

331
00:14:51,801 --> 00:14:53,795
They would probably
kill you to silence you

332
00:14:53,796 --> 00:14:56,093
even if you returned it.

333
00:14:56,603 --> 00:14:57,998
What does that mean? That's terrifying.

334
00:14:57,999 --> 00:15:00,493
Princess Iris has always
worn this ring on her hand,

335
00:15:00,494 --> 00:15:02,004
and she really cares about it.

336
00:15:02,603 --> 00:15:03,901
Whatever happens,

337
00:15:03,902 --> 00:15:05,493
you have to keep it with you at all times

338
00:15:05,494 --> 00:15:07,301
and not let anyone see it.

339
00:15:17,598 --> 00:15:20,520
I had no idea that necklace
was so dangerous.

340
00:15:21,299 --> 00:15:24,045
Good job, Lord Dustiness.

341
00:15:24,610 --> 00:15:25,405
Thank you.

342
00:15:26,398 --> 00:15:27,916
Speaking of which,

343
00:15:28,107 --> 00:15:28,207
you were of no use that night either.

344
00:15:33,415 --> 00:15:34,592
Could they

345
00:15:35,204 --> 00:15:38,301
have been trying to help me?

346
00:15:39,098 --> 00:15:40,206
If so,

347
00:15:40,207 --> 00:15:41,409
the thief who is said to be out there

348
00:15:41,410 --> 00:15:44,607
would really be a chivalrous thief.

349
00:15:44,608 --> 00:15:46,013
How can that be possible?

350
00:15:46,014 --> 00:15:49,190
But if that is true,

351
00:15:49,191 --> 00:15:51,699
I have to say they are pretty cool.

352
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:53,801
Huh?

353
00:15:54,697 --> 00:15:56,493
Are you talking about
the person wearing the mask?

354
00:15:56,494 --> 00:15:58,310
He's really cool, isn't he?

355
00:15:58,311 --> 00:16:00,493
I was drawn to that mask

356
00:16:00,494 --> 00:16:02,498
and the black clothes.

357
00:16:02,499 --> 00:16:03,410
If I see him again,

358
00:16:03,411 --> 00:16:05,213
I will definitely beg for an autograph.

359
00:16:06,006 --> 00:16:07,914
Oh no, what should I do?

360
00:16:07,915 --> 00:16:10,510
I wish I could brag
to everyone that that is me.

361
00:16:11,208 --> 00:16:13,196
What's wrong, Kazuma?

362
00:16:13,197 --> 00:16:15,593
You've been giggling all the time.
It's kind of disgusting, you know.

363
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:19,410
What exactly are you laughing about?

364
00:16:21,493 --> 00:16:25,410
The chivalrous thief

365
00:16:26,097 --> 00:16:27,702
looks really handsome.

366
00:16:28,410 --> 00:16:29,904
Given the circumstances,

367
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:33,416
she surely could not have guessed
who the thief was, could she?

368
00:16:34,696 --> 00:16:38,206
Their actions suggest

369
00:16:38,207 --> 00:16:40,503
that they are concerned about me.

370
00:16:41,098 --> 00:16:49,197
I might have fallen for
that chivalrous thief.

371
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:51,394
Okay.

372
00:16:51,395 --> 00:16:52,805
I'll reveal my identity then.

373
00:16:52,806 --> 00:16:54,394
W-What's the matter, Kazuma?

374
00:16:54,395 --> 00:16:55,909
-Why did you suddenly stand up?
-What are you doing?

375
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:57,493
Do you need to pee? Do you need to pee?

376
00:16:57,494 --> 00:16:58,909
-You're such a pain.
-Do you want to see me pee?

377
00:16:58,910 --> 00:17:00,100
-I am very sorry.
-Okay.

378
00:17:00,101 --> 00:17:02,696
-I'll get this rude guy out of here right away.
-I'll just pee right here for you to see.

379
00:17:02,697 --> 00:17:04,947
Hey, quickly let go.

380
00:17:04,948 --> 00:17:06,591
Otherwise, I'll use Drain Touch.

381
00:17:06,592 --> 00:17:07,597
That chief

382
00:17:09,005 --> 00:17:11,195
with the silver hair has me wondering

383
00:17:11,909 --> 00:17:16,216
about him and his whereabouts.

384
00:17:23,389 --> 00:17:24,405
Konosuba.

385
00:17:25,502 --> 00:17:27,212
It makes me a little sad to leave.

386
00:17:31,497 --> 00:17:32,909
Older brother.

387
00:17:32,910 --> 00:17:35,207
I have a wish.

388
00:17:37,209 --> 00:17:38,815
I have something to say

389
00:17:38,816 --> 00:17:40,092
before you bring up that wish.

390
00:17:43,608 --> 00:17:47,315
This person has defeated
many Leaders of the Devil King's Army.

391
00:17:47,816 --> 00:17:48,904
Eventually,

392
00:17:48,905 --> 00:17:51,306
he might beat the Devil King.

393
00:17:51,903 --> 00:17:53,602
Even though it is hard to do

394
00:17:53,603 --> 00:17:54,994
and not very likely to happen.

395
00:17:56,001 --> 00:17:59,206
Could you kindly offer some words
of encouragement to him,

396
00:17:59,207 --> 00:18:01,707
who is courageous enough
to face the challenges head-on?

397
00:18:02,303 --> 00:18:04,894
What is she talking about now?

398
00:18:05,703 --> 00:18:07,211
Defeat the Devil King?

399
00:18:08,101 --> 00:18:09,211
Really?

400
00:18:09,212 --> 00:18:12,590
Are you really going
to defeat the Devil King?

401
00:18:13,091 --> 00:18:15,806
How could that possi--

402
00:18:21,197 --> 00:18:23,701
Well. If there is a chance,
it appears like a good idea to go

403
00:18:23,702 --> 00:18:28,306
and subdue the Devil King.

404
00:18:30,707 --> 00:18:33,112
Older brother, you can surely do it!

405
00:18:33,113 --> 00:18:35,410
Please do your best
to repel the Devil King!

406
00:18:36,301 --> 00:18:38,399
You keep calling him "older brother."

407
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,519
Stop calling him that.

408
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:43,602
You have your own real brother, right?

409
00:18:43,603 --> 00:18:46,107
Why don't you go and flirt with him?

410
00:18:46,108 --> 00:18:49,084
One day, I will personally
put an end to the Devil King.

411
00:18:49,085 --> 00:18:50,795
Kazuma doesn't need to action.

412
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,196
He is older brother.

413
00:18:53,197 --> 00:18:54,826
What is wrong with calling him

414
00:18:54,827 --> 00:18:56,571
"older brother"?

415
00:18:56,572 --> 00:19:00,513
Besides, there's no point in
you defeating the Devil King.

416
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:03,591
I hope that older brother
will defeat the Devil King.

417
00:19:03,592 --> 00:19:05,059
I just told you not to call him that!

418
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:06,602
And yet you keep calling him
"older brother"!

419
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:08,896
Are you challenging me?

420
00:19:08,897 --> 00:19:10,189
D-Do you want to fight?

421
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:12,483
The royal family is very strong, you know.

422
00:19:12,484 --> 00:19:13,984
-Hey, stop it, Megumin!
-What are you talking about?

423
00:19:13,985 --> 00:19:15,543
-Clearly, you and Princess Iris
-Even the royal family would not be

424
00:19:15,544 --> 00:19:17,315
-became closer yesterday.
-able to stop my explosion magic!

425
00:19:17,316 --> 00:19:21,085
- Princess Iris, please calm down.
-Fine, experience it for yourself then.

426
00:19:21,086 --> 00:19:23,628
-You clearly haven't fought with anyone else.
-My Exterion is also very strong, okay?

427
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,097
So what?

428
00:19:26,607 --> 00:19:28,707
What is your wish?

429
00:19:28,708 --> 00:19:30,084
Go ahead and say it.

430
00:19:32,488 --> 00:19:33,487
My wish…

431
00:19:34,109 --> 00:19:35,701
My wish is…

432
00:19:44,307 --> 00:19:46,815
The outcome of our game
has not been decided yet.

433
00:19:47,394 --> 00:19:50,706
Please play with me again sometime.

434
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,357
Konosuba.

435
00:20:06,502 --> 00:20:08,200
Hey, shut up!

436
00:20:08,201 --> 00:20:09,491
The neighbors would be irritated.

437
00:20:09,492 --> 00:20:11,309
Go yell in the suburbs.

438
00:20:11,310 --> 00:20:12,491
Are you kidding me?

439
00:20:12,492 --> 00:20:13,913
I can't believe you would
step in at that critical juncture.

440
00:20:13,914 --> 00:20:16,491
-If you had not brought up the Devil King,
-Next, please sign this for me.

441
00:20:16,492 --> 00:20:19,611
